---
export const prerender = true;

import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ProtectedEmail from '~/components/ProtectedEmail.astro';
import { buildHreflang } from '~/lib/i18n';

const hreflang = buildHreflang('/en/privacy', 'en');
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy policy · Le Geai Informatique"
  description="Privacy policy of legeai-informatique.fr: data processing, cookies, anonymous statistics, likes, comments, GDPR rights."
  noindex={true}
  lang="en"
  hreflang={hreflang}
>
  <article class="legal">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <header class="head">
        <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          This page describes what we do, or do not, with the data that passes
          through this site. The principle is simple: we collect as little as
          possible, and we tell you precisely what is kept.
        </p>
      </header>

      <section>
        <h2>Data controller</h2>
        <p>
          The data controller is Le Geai Informatique, a micro-entreprise
          whose details appear on the
          <a href="/en/legal-notice">legal notice</a> page.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What we do not do</h2>
        <p>
          The site uses <strong>no advertising network</strong>, drops
          <strong>no third-party tracking cookie</strong> (no Google Analytics,
          no Facebook pixel, no Hotjar). No data is resold, shared with
          commercial third parties, or used for profiling.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What we collect</h2>

        <h3>1. Technical server logs</h3>
        <p>
          Like any web server, ours keeps technical journals: IP address,
          browser, page consulted, response code, timestamp. These logs are
          kept for at most <strong>30 days</strong>, for security, diagnostics
          and the prevention of abuse.
        </p>

        <h3>2. Anonymous traffic statistics</h3>
        <p>
          We measure the audience of our pages, in particular journal
          articles, to understand what interests our readers. These statistics
          are <strong>strictly anonymous</strong>: we record the URL
          consulted, the rounded timestamp, the device type (mobile or
          desktop) and the entry source (search engine, direct link, etc.).
          No identifying data is kept. No cookie, no persistent identifier.
        </p>

        <h3>3. Contact form</h3>
        <p>
          When you write to us via the <a href="/en/contact">contact form</a>,
          we keep what you have entered: surname, optionally first name, the
          means of contact you indicate (email, telephone or postal address),
          subject and message. This data is stored in our administration
          interface and kept for the time required to answer and follow up
          your enquiry (generally 3 years, the minimum legal duration for
          commercial documents).
        </p>

        <h3>4. Likes and comments (forthcoming)</h3>
        <p>
          We plan to add the ability to react to articles soon: a system of
          <strong>anonymous likes</strong> and a system of
          <strong>comments</strong>. When these are active, this policy will
          be clarified. By anticipation:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Likes</strong>: we shall record only the article
            identifier and the date of the like. No personal data is
            associated.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Comments</strong>: we shall ask for a name (which may be
            a pseudonym), optionally an email (never published, used only to
            notify you of a reply if you wish), and the comment. Comments are
            moderated before publication.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>5. Minimal anti-spam fingerprint</h3>
        <p>
          To prevent massive automated submissions (contact form, future
          likes and comments), we compute a technical fingerprint from your
          IP address, your browser and a secret salt proper to our site.
          This fingerprint is:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>hashed</strong> irreversibly (SHA-256), which means it
            does not allow tracing back to your IP or your identity;
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>kept for at most 90 days</strong>, the time to detect
            suspicious repeated submissions;
          </li>
          <li>
            used <strong>only</strong> for moderation and rate limiting. It
            is never cross-referenced with other data to identify you.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          The site uses <strong>no audience or advertising cookie</strong>.
          It may set strictly technical cookies necessary for the proper
          functioning of the interface (display preferences, session). These
          cookies do not require your consent, in accordance with article 82
          of the French Data Protection Act.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Data recipients</h2>
        <p>
          The data is not transmitted to any third party, nor sold, nor
          rented. It is accessible only to Le Geai Informatique, in its
          internal administration interface, for managing relationships with
          those who contact us and for improving the site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Hosting and location</h2>
        <p>
          The data is hosted in France, on a virtual private server operated
          by OVH SAS. No transfer of data outside the European Union is made.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          Under the GDPR and the French Data Protection Act, you have the
          following rights over your personal data:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>right of access to your data;</li>
          <li>right of rectification;</li>
          <li>right to erasure;</li>
          <li>right to restriction of processing;</li>
          <li>right to portability;</li>
          <li>right to object.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise these rights, write to
          <ProtectedEmail user="administration" domain="legeai-editions.com" lang="en" />
          stating your request. We shall reply within one month.
        </p>
        <p>
          For entirely anonymous data (traffic statistics, hashed anti-spam
          fingerprints), it is technically not possible to find yours in
          particular, so the rights of access and erasure cannot be applied
          individually.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you consider that your rights are not respected, you may lodge
          a complaint with the CNIL:
          <a href="https://www.cnil.fr" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cnil.fr</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Updates to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          This policy may be updated to reflect legal, technical or
          functional changes (in particular the opening of likes and
          comments). The last significant update is from May 2026.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal { padding-top: 8rem; padding-bottom: 5rem; }
  .head { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 3rem; padding: 0 1.5rem; }
  h1 { margin-top: 1rem; font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.8rem); }
  .lead {
    max-width: 620px;
    margin: 1.5rem auto 0;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  section { padding: 0 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  section h2 {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.6rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  section h3 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--color-dore);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  section h3:first-of-type { margin-top: 0.5rem; }
  section p { color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  section ul {
    list-style: none;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  section li {
    padding: 0.4rem 0 0.4rem 1.4rem;
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  section li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 1.05rem;
    width: 8px;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--color-dore);
  }
  section a {
    color: var(--color-dore);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    transition: border-color 0.3s ease;
  }
  section a:hover { border-bottom-color: var(--color-dore); }
  section strong { color: var(--color-text); font-weight: 700; }
</style>
